Executive Committee of the All Progressives Congress (APC) in ward 10 Estako West local government area of Edo has lifted the suspension order on Comrade Adams Oshiomhole. APC National Vice Chairman (South South), Hilliard Eta, announced this at a briefing in Abuja. He said the National Secretariat of APC was notified of the development by members and officials from Oshiomhole’s ward. (The Nation) Executives of the All Progressives Congress (APC) in ward 10 Estako West local government area of Edo have lifted the suspension order on Comrade Adams Oshiomhole. Details Later… June 20, 2020 In "Politics" Abuja (Sundiata Post) - A Federal Capital Territory (FCT) High Court in Jabi on Wednesday ordered the suspension of the National Chairman of the All Progressive Congress (APC), Adams Oshiomhole, pending the determination of a substantive suit. The judge, Danlami Senchi, gave the order following an application of interlocutory injunction… March 4, 2020 In "Top Stories" •APC Acting National Chairman, Senator Isiaka Ajimobi ABUJA - The All Progressives Congress (APC) on Tuesday elevated Senator Abiola Ajimobi to serve as its acting National Chairman after the Court of Appeal upheld the suspension of Adams Oshiomhole. Senator Ajimobi was the party’s Deputy National Chairman for the southern region… June 17, 2020 In "Politics"